  "doc_id": "26034",
  "text": "The presence of oxidative stress was tested by assay of the lipoperoxidative end-product malondialdehyde (MDA) as free fraction in the total RBC lysate and plasma. The thiobarbituric acid test was used, but its specificity was evaluated in some experiments by direct HPLC analysis of MDA as described previously [CITATION_1] , with only minor modifications. Briefly, RBC suspensions at a Ht of 30% were subjected to hypotonic lysis, and after perchloric acid extraction [CITATION_2] , the supernatant was filtered through 0.22 m pore filters and subjected to HPLC. An LC-18T reversed-phase column (15 cm ϫ 4.6 mm i.d.; Supelco) and isocratic conditions were used. The mobile phase was a mixture of 500 mL/L NaH 2 PO 4 , pH 8, and 500 mL/L methanol, and the flow rate was 1 mL/min. The elution time for MDA was 16.3 Ϯ 0.6 min. An MDA calibrator was prepared by acidic hydrolysis of a solution of 1,1,3,3-tetrahydroxypropane.",
